##Past Affairs of Wuhan Health Protection Committee

Micro Signal biz-leaders

Function introduction, define Chinese commercial power

By Feng Chao

By Feng Chao

Source: biz-leaders

One

The Chinese knew about a virus, and they knew about an organization that published data called the Health Commission. The organization is called the Health Commission for Short.

Health committees at all levels are renamed from health and Family Planning Committees (bureaus) at all levels. The new name added the word "health" and was changed from top to bottom, from March 2018 until the spring of 2019.

The sub-province-level division, the Health Commission of a provincial capital, is one of them, as is Wuhan.

The official website of Wuhan Health Commission lists the 16 functions of Wuhan Health Commission.

Article 3: To formulate and implement the city-wide plan for Disease Prevention and control and the intervention measures for serious public health problems endangering the People's Health; to organize the implementation of immunization programmes; and to organize the monitoring of infectious diseases. To be responsible for health emergency work, organize and guide the prevention and control of public health emergencies and medical and health rescue of various public health emergencies.

There are two duties:

On the website of Wuhan Health Commission, there are relevant information about open government affairs.

The website publishes the annual report of the Municipal Health Commission on the work of government information disclosure in 2019. Part V of the report refers to "problems with the disclosure of information" , "first, we need to step up our efforts to effectively take the initiative to open up our work. There is still a gap between the active disclosure of information from a working point of view and the public's keen interest in access to information, and more information closely related to the public needs to be made public from a public point of view.".

Two

On July 21,2016, the discipline inspection team assigned to the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and Family Planning (later renamed the Commission of Health and Family Planning) was officially established, according to the Wuhan Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision.

At the end of 2017, the Discipline Inspection Commission published a paper entitled "assignment to the Municipal Commission for Health and Family Planning: Our Year" . According to the article, "In the past year, the discipline inspection unit has received a total of 219 complaint letters and visits, and has handled 196 of them, with a handling rate of 90 percent. 30 cases have been placed on file, involving three department-level cadres, 27 people at or below section level, and 30 people have been given disciplinary measures against the Party and the government, of which 12 have been handed over to the judiciary. " "In the past year, the party leadership has conducted 480 talks on clean government, and 96 talks on reminders and criticism of education. ".

In April 2017, the discipline inspection team conducted a work interview with Chen Yun, secretary of the leading party group and Full-time Vice-president of the Red Cross Society of the city, who ranked last in the 2016 assessment of the city's responsibility system for party conduct and clean government.

The Commission wrote in an article titled "assignment to the Discipline Inspection Team of the Municipal Commission of Health and Family Planning: Interviewing the top leaders of the lowest-ranking units in the assessment of the Party's Work Style and clean government responsibility system" that it was called "Foshan" 

"The interview pointed out the problems of the city Red Cross Society in the construction of Party conduct and clean government, such as the indepth education of clean government, the incompleteness of clean government system, and the weak sense of responsibility of the main leading bodies, "We should draw lessons, reflect deeply, probe into the problems in the education of an honest and clean government and the construction of work style, and establish and improve a long-term effective mechanism to promote clean and competent cadres. ".

In 2018, the Discipline Inspection Unit compiled the "warning record of typical cases of violations of law and discipline in the health and Family Planning System in Wuhan" (hereinafter referred to as "warning record") . This is a booklet, compiled and printed more than 1000 copies, distributed to the Municipal Commission of Health and Family Planning organs and the Commission of 27 medical and health institutions.

According to an article by the Commission for Discipline Inspection, "The 22 typical cases included in the warning record were selected from the disciplinary violations that have occurred in the city's health statistics system since the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) . The cases involved people who were 'top leaders' of the work unit, as well as members of the team and middle-level cadres, and covered acts of corruption and bribery, violation of the spirit of the eight regulations and omission and disorderly conduct. "

"Warning Record" , photo from Wuhan Discipline Inspection Commission official website

In May 2019, the discipline inspection team and the Municipal Health and Health Commission jointly held the "Red Line of understanding the law and discipline" Party discipline knowledge competition, which was broadcast live on a platform of fighting fish.

According to "business figures" incomplete statistics, in the four years before 2020, Wuhan Health and Health Commission reported a number of violations of the law and regulations.

In 2016, Cheng Ming, deputy director of the Qingshan District Health and Family Planning Commission, and others illegally accepted requests from businesses. From November 29 to December 2,2015, Cheng Ming, deputy director of the District Health and Family Planning Commission, Huang Jianjun, deputy director of the city Ninth Hospital, Tan Yue, deputy director of the administration of the Western pharmacy, and others went to Tianjin for a study tour, accepting business banquets from enterprises in violation of regulations four times. On June 7,2016, the Qingshan District, Wuhan Commission for Discipline Inspection Gave Cheng Ming a severe inner-party warning; the District Commission for Health and Family Planning Gave Huang Jianjun Administrative Demerit; and the District Commission for Health and Family Planning gave Tan Yue a severe inner-party warning.

Ryhming, the former deputy party secretary and Secretary of the Discipline Inspection Commission of the Xinzhou District Health and Family Planning Commission in Wuhan, spent the Spring Festival period from 2014 to 2016 and during my hospital stay, received under the Red Cross Hospital, maternal and child health care hospital and other units sent cash, Wechat Hongbao, gifts and other total of more than 35,400 yuan. The Xinzhou District Disciplinary Commission gave Ryhming a disciplinary measure to remove him from party posts, making it clear that his rank had been downgraded from deputy to official.

In 2017, the Commission of Discipline Inspection found that Jiangxia District's health-care system had problems with falsified data, falsely reporting the number of basic United States Public Health Service and the number of services provided. Jiang Xia district health and Family Planning Commission responsible for the accountability.

District Health and Family Planning Commission Disease Control Section chief Gao Yutang administrative demerit, district health and Family Planning Commission deputy investigator people's livelihood administrative warning. The personnel who are directly responsible and in charge of the primary medical institutions are also subject to disciplinary and organizational sanctions.

"This is a microcosm of Wuhan's cutting into formalism and bureaucracy. Since April last year, Wuhan has been carrying out a special governance campaign of not assuming responsibility and not acting, and strict investigation has been conducted against those who occupy seats and do not act,"Changjiang daily said in an article.

Three

The official website of the Wuhan Health Commission released the "2018 Wuhan Health Development Bulletin" .

The total number of medical and health institutions in the city reached 6,340, an increase of 269 over the previous year, the report showed. There are 398 hospitals, 5,853 primary medical and health institutions and 79 specialized public health institutions. There were 44 more hospitals than the previous year.

There are 61 level III hospitals (including 27 military hospitals) , 64 level II hospitals, 164 level I hospitals and 109 ungraded hospitals) , according to the classification of hospitals. According to the number of beds, there are 44 beds in 100 ~ 199 hospitals, 28 beds in 200 ~ 499 hospitals, 10 beds in 500 ~ 799 hospitals, and 34 beds in 800 hospitals and above.

Among the specialized public health institutions, there are 17 centers for Disease Control and Prevention, including one at the provincial level, one at the municipal level, 14 at the district level, and one in the industry.

Wuhan's medical strength, the national leader. Under normal circumstances, the doctor can choose to go to Wuhan.

In June 2019, the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and United States Public Health Service announced the budget for 2019. The budget comes from the financial allocation of 38,269,100 yuan.

In accordance with the requirements of the law of the People's Republic of China on the Prevention and control of infectious diseases and the measures for the implementation of the Law of the People's Republic of China on maternal and child health care, this budget is mainly used for AIDS, tuberculosis, schistosomiasis, immunization programmes, maternal and child health care, Prenatal Health check-ups and so on.

The Wuhan Municipal Health and Population Ageing Commission released an analysis of the situation in Wuhan in 2018. By the end of 2018, the total registered population of the city was 8.837 million, of which 1.8794 million were over 60 years old, accounting for 21.27 percent of the total population.

Image courtesy of the 2018 Wuhan Population Ageing Analysis

An aging city. The old people are many, means the foundation disease possibly many, the resistance is poor.
